"title": "8353: tolerance",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8353",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The virtue of being prepared to accept people and their viewpoints. While commended within the church, Scripture insists that believers must have a vital concern for maintaining and defending the truth.</p>\n<h2>Toleration should be exercised for the benefit of those whose faith is weak</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:1\">ROM 14:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:2-Rom14:6\">ROM 14:2–14:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:13-Rom14:22\">ROM 14:13–14:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:8-1Cor8:13\">1CO 8:8–8:13</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of tolerance</h2>\n<p>By Jesus Christ:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:13-Matt19:14\">MAT 19:13–19:14</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:13-Mark10:14\">MRK 10:13–10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:15-Luke18:16\">LUK 18:15–18:16</a> <em>in contrast to the disciples' intolerance</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:33-Mark9:36\">MRK 9:33–9:36</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:46-Luke9:47\">LUK 9:46–9:47</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:38-Mark9:40\">MRK 9:38–9:40</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:49-Luke9:50\">LUK 9:49–9:50</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:17-Phil1:18\">PHP 1:17–1:18</a> <em>by Paul</em></p>\n<h2>Limits to toleration</h2>\n<h3>Evil cannot be tolerated</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:13\">HAB 1:13</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Wickedness cannot be tolerated</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:2\">REV 2:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Serious doctrinal errors cannot be tolerated</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal2:4\">GAL 2:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:1-2Thess2:3\">2TH 2:1–2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:3-1Tim6:5\">1TI 6:3–6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:20-1Tim6:21\">1TI 6:20–6:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Tim4:3-2Tim4:4\">2TI 4:3–4:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:1\">2PE 2:1</a></p>\n<h3>Sexual sin should not be tolerated</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:1-1Cor5:5\">1CO 5:1–5:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:18-1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:18–6:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:14\">REV 2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Idolatry should not be tolerated</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor10:7\">1CO 10:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John5:21\">1JN 5:21</a></p>",
